						               													<description>Waterloo 2015 is an abstract game about the battle of Waterloo in june 1815.&amp;#10;There are NO DICE and NO combat CARDS in this game.&amp;#10;You will only find Event cards, in order to ensure replayability.&amp;#10;You have to carefully plan your moves and assaults, like in the Chess...&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This game uses hexagonal zones, and some zones are crucial : Hougoumont, Mont St.Jean, La Haye Sainte, etc...&amp;#10;In order to win, you have to control a certain number of crucial zones.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;One player controls the Allied army (Anglo-Prussian), and the other controls the French army. Each army includes 3 types of units : infantry (normal and elite), cavalry (normal and elite), and artillery. You charge and pursue with the cavalry, you bombard and defend with the artillery, BUT you control the terrain with the infantry... &amp;#10;Each zone contains up to 8 units.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Turn sequence :&amp;#10;Allied Approach.&amp;#10;French Approach.&amp;#10;French Engagement.&amp;#10;Allied Engagement.&amp;#10;Reorganisation.&amp;#10;Victory conditions.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
